news.title: Landlords raise rent on more than half of properties in England: ONS
news.para: The Office for National Statistics (ONS) analysed data collected every 12 months about privately-rented homes, revisiting the properties to track price changes over time.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group Holdings forecasts loss of up to about $2 billion
news.para: The Shenzhen-based company earlier this month, published its long-delayed results for fiscal 2021 in which it reported a loss of 13.26 billion yuan.

news.title: Despite SC order, Chandigarh mayor backs share-wise registration of properties
news.para: In a meeting with UT adviser Dharam Pal at the UT secretariat, Sector 9 here on Friday, Gupta took up issues regarding sale/purchase of shares in property and permission of temporary roof in central courtyard open to sky pertaining to sectors 7, 8 and 26 on Madhya Marg.

news.title: Bidhannagar cops ask New Town RWAs to furnish list of tenants
news.para: The move was initiated after Bidhannagar Police unearthed a racket of fake call centre operators who were working out of flats and houses in New Town and Salt Lake.

news.title: Severe penalty soon on illegal buildings in Kerala
news.para: Stressing on the need to plug tax loss, Rajesh said that an extensive inspection shall be carried out to identify buildings that underwent alterations without getting the approval of respective local bodies.

news.title: File roadmap to cut emissions within 15 days in Haryana, brick kilns told
news.para: Officials said the proposal, which should be backed by scientific evidence, will be then forwarded to the Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM).

news.title: No bidders for Ahmedabad civic body's costly plots
news.para: A total of seven plots in some of the prime areas of the city were in offing with a base price of Rs 499.72 crore. These plots were located in Bodakdev, Thaltej, Vastral and Nikol.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body's revenue plan from building, licence fees
news.para: With the civic body expecting the state to sanction the proposal to allow an extra floor on residential buildings in Salt Lake, BMC, while tabling the Budget, proposed an earning of Rs 32 crore from building plan sanction fees from April 1.

news.title: Second edition of The Economic Times Real Estate Awards 2023-WEST rewards excellence in industry
news.para: The second edition of The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2023 – West was graced by the presence of chief guest Dr. Sanjay Kolte, CEO, Pune Smart City Development Corporation.

news.title: Govt planning to advance rural 'housing for all' deadline by three months to December 2023
news.para: As part of this initiative, a revised deadline for constructing 29.5 million houses under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Gramin) by March 2024 was set.

news.title: DDA's luxury flats in Dwarka to be up for bidding by Diwali
news.para: The project site is located at Sector 19B. "We are making our best efforts to complete the project by November. Thereafter, applications will be invited from buyers and a computerised draw of lots conducted.

news.title: Bombay HC orders occupancy certificate for 27 Virar buildings
news.para: Velson Developers and eight others, including flat owners across nine buildings, had last year moved the HC to challenge an August 2022 municipal order rejecting OC, citing lapsing of a green nod.

news.title: Reducing embodied emissions in building design could save up to 6 gigatonnes of carbon by 2050
news.para: ​Researchers from the University of Cambridge and Bath, UK, devised a computer model and used it to estimate that these recommendations could also save between 28 and 44 per cent of annual heating and cooling costs, using technology that is currently available.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 252 crore worth 'Ambience Tower' in Delhi's Shalimar Bagh
news.para: The immovable property is named Ambience Tower and it belongs to a company called Ambience Towers Pvt Ltd, a firm of the Ambience Group promoted by Raj Singh Gehlot, the agency said in a statement.

news.title: Government proposes tax relief for REITs, InVITS
news.para: However, the government on Friday proposed to soften the tax impact on Real estate investment trusts (REITs) and Infrastructure investment trusts (InVITs) through amendments to the Finance Bill 2023.
